Colombia Stocks: ETB, Grupo Inversiones Suramericana, Tablemac

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-06-07T20:32:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/colombia-stocks-etb-grupo-inversiones-suramericana-tablemac.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.2 percent to 14,416.15, while the
Colcap Index declined 0.2 percent to 1,750.15.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota SA (ETB CB), the
state-run phone company serving  Colombia ’s capital, rose 3.6
percent to 745 pesos, a six-month high, on expectations that
Bogota’s mayor’s office will submit a proposal to open the way
for the city to sell part or all of its 86.6 percent stake in
the company, said Santiago Melo, an analyst at brokerage Alianza
Valores SA.  Telefonica SA (TEF)  ,  Spain ’s biggest phone operator,
hasn’t ruled out the possibility of buying a stake in ETB,
Alfonso Gomez, head of Telefonica in Colombia, told Caracol
radio on June 3, according to the station’s website.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR)  , the
parent company of Colombia’s largest bank, rose 0.9 percent to
39,980 pesos, a one-week high. The company plans to expand
abroad and increase revenue from overseas to at least 50 percent
of the company’s total within 10 years, Chief Financial Officer
Andres Bernal told the daily La Republica.  The Medellin-based holding company currently gets between
15 percent and 20 percent of its revenue from abroad, Bernal
told the newspaper.  Tableros & Maderas de Caldas SA (TABLEMA CB), a Colombian
wood-products maker, rose to a record in Bogota as investors bet
the planned opening of a medium-density fiberboard plant will
boost sales, said Nicolas Velasquez, an analyst at Celfin
Capital. The stock advanced 0.8 percent to 13 pesos, the highest
closing price since 1998.  To contact the reporter on this story:
